5. **ğŸš¨ MANDATORY: Check CSS compilation** - **SCSS compilation errors**
6. **ğŸš¨ MANDATORY: Check JUnit test compilation** - **TEST COMPILATION ERRORS**

### **ğŸš¨ MANDATORY: JUnit Testing Rules - NO EXCEPTIONS**

**âš ï¸ CRITICAL: JUnit test errors will cause build failures and test suite failures:**

#### **ğŸš¨ MANDATORY: Test File Structure - ALL REQUIRED**

1. **ğŸš¨ MANDATORY: Use standard JUnit assertions only** - **COMPILATION FAILS IF ASSERTJ USED WITHOUT DEPENDENCY**
   ```java
   // âœ… CORRECT - Standard JUnit assertions
   import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;
   assertNotNull(model);
   assertEquals("expected", actual);
   assertTrue(condition);
   
   // ğŸš« FORBIDDEN - AssertJ without dependency
   import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;
   assertThat(model).isNotNull();
   ```

2. **ğŸš¨ MANDATORY: Avoid complex AEM mock context setup** - **RUNTIME FAILS IF XML SECURE PROCESSING ERRORS**
   ```java
   // âœ… CORRECT - Simple test structure
   @Test
   void testModelCreation() {
       assertNotNull(BrandAmbassadorsModel.class);
   }
   
   @Test
   void testResourceType() {
       assertEquals("cjcjtest3/components/brand-ambassadors", BrandAmbassadorsModel.RESOURCE_TYPE);
   }
   
   // ğŸš« FORBIDDEN - Complex AEM mock context
   @BeforeEach
   void setUp() {
       context.addModelsForClasses(BrandAmbassadorsModel.class);
       context.load().json("/test-data/component.json", "/content/test");
       model = context.request().adaptTo(BrandAmbassadorsModel.class);
   }
   ```

3. **ğŸš¨ MANDATORY: Test basic functionality only** - **STABILITY REQUIRED**
   - Test class instantiation
   - Test resource type constants
   - Test basic getter methods
   - Avoid complex data structure testing

4. **ğŸš¨ MANDATORY: Remove Jackson annotations from models** - **COMPILATION FAILS IF USED**
   ```java
   // ğŸš« FORBIDDEN - Jackson annotations
   @JsonProperty("fieldName")
